  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Peel and chop the <strong>sweet potatoes</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Top and tail the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, then slice into half moons</p>\n<p>Add both to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and put into the oven for 18-20 min or until tender</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the<strong> sushi rice</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p>\n<p>Add the drained rice with 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Tip: Don't let the water fully boil as this will make the rice stick to the pot!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p>\n<p>After 15 min, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving – this is your <strong>sticky rice</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: Don't peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get perfectly fluffy rice!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2250-Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">While the rice is cooking, boil half a kettle</span></p>\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel and grate the <strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
